cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper discusses the development and evaluation of a neural machine translation system, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically machine translation. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the evaluation of the translation output involves automatic and human evaluation, which could relate to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories that deal with evaluation metrics and human perception.
